    "In the last step, the corresponding derivatives of Eq.",
    "(15) were calculated with respect to z, z rather than the more usual pair x, y (i.e.",
    "the complex plane) are used.",
    "They have the same properties as \"normal\" derivatives (i.e.",
    "linearity, product rule, chain rule, conjugation), but can be used more efficiently with the complex lens equation."
